#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring clients to use &rmt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: meta
#: rmt_client.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure any machine running SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 12 or newer to register against the RMT server and download software updates from there"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: date
#: rmt_client.xml:17
#, no-c-format
msgid "2023-06-02"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:24
#, no-c-format
msgid "Any machine running &sle; 12 or newer can be configured to register against &rmt; and download software updates from there, instead of communicating directly with &scc;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "Register with the &rmt; server over HTTP"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "We recommend registering with the &rmt; server over a secured HTTPS protocol (all examples in this documentation use it). However, you can also register with the &rmt; server over an insecure HTTP protocol. Use this approach only if your setup benefits from it <emphasis role=\"bold\">and</emphasis> only in a trusted environment where security is not crucial."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "To configure clients to use the &rmt; server, use one of the following methods:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:46
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provide the required information with boot parameters. See <xref linkend=\"sec-rmt-client-parameters\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure the clients using an &ay; profile. See <xref linkend=\"sec-rmt-client-autoyast\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use the <command>rmt-client-setup</command> command. See <xref linkend=\"sec-rmt-client-clientsetupscript\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use the &yast; registration module during installation or later. See <xref linkend=\"sec-rmt-client-yast\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "CA certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you need the CA certificate of the &rmt; server, find it at <filename>/etc/rmt/ssl/rmt-ca.crt</filename> and <literal>https://<replaceable>RMT_SERVER</replaceable>/rmt.crt</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring clients with boot parameters"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "Any client can be configured to use &rmt; by providing the <option>regurl</option> parameter during machine boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "The parameter needs to be entered as <option>regurl=<replaceable>RMT_SERVER_URL</replaceable></option> . The URL needs to be in the following format: <literal>https://<replaceable>FQDN</replaceable></literal> , with <replaceable>FQDN</replaceable> being the fully qualified host name of the &rmt; server. It must be identical to the FQDN of the server certificate used on the &rmt; server. Example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: rmt_client.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "regurl=https://rmt.&exampledomain;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Beware of typing errors"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make sure the values you enter are correct. If <option>regurl</option> has not been specified correctly, the registration of the update source fails."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change of &rmt; server certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the &rmt; server gets a new certificate from an untrusted CA, the clients need to retrieve the new CA certificate file. &yast; displays a dialog for importing a new certificate. If you confirm importing the new certificate, the old one is replaced with the new one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring clients with &ay; profile"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Clients can be configured to register with the &rmt; server via an &ay; profile. To learn about creating &ay; profiles and preparing for automatic installation, refer to the <emphasis>&ay; Guide</emphasis> . In this section, only &rmt; specific configuration is described."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "To configure &rmt; specific data using &ay;, follow the steps for the relevant version of the &rmt; client."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "As &rootuser;, start &yast; and select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Miscellaneous</guimenu> <guimenu>Autoinstallation</guimenu> </menuchoice> to start the graphical &ay; front-end."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "From a command line, you can start the graphical &ay; front-end with the <command>yast2 autoyast</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open an existing profile using <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Open</guimenu></menuchoice> . Create a profile based on the current system's configuration using <menuchoice> <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> <guimenu>Create Reference Profile</guimenu> </menuchoice> , or work with an empty profile."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Software</guimenu> <guimenu>Product Registration</guimenu> </menuchoice> . An overview of the current configuration is shown."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check <guimenu>Register the Product</guimenu> , set the URL of the &rmt; server in <guimenu>Use Specific Server URL Instead of the Default</guimenu> , and you can set the <guimenu>Optional SSL Server Certificate URL</guimenu> . The possible values for the server URL are the same as for the kernel parameter <option>regurl</option> . For the SSL certificate location, you can use either HTTP or HTTPS based URLs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Perform all other configurations needed for the systems to be deployed, then click <guimenu>Finish</guimenu> to return to the main screen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Save As</guimenu> </menuchoice> and enter a file name for the profile, such as <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:195
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring clients with <command>rmt-client-setup</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <command>/usr/share/rmt/public/tools/rmt-client-setup</command> script is provided in the package <package>rmt-server</package> . This script allows you to configure a client machine to use an &rmt; server. It can also be used to reconfigure an existing client to use a different &rmt; server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:205
#, no-c-format
msgid "To configure a client machine to use &rmt; with <command>rmt-client-setup</command> , follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download <filename>rmt-client-setup</filename> from the &rmt; server:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: rmt_client.xml:215
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>curl http://<replaceable>RMT_SERVER</replaceable>/tools/rmt-client-setup --output rmt-client-setup</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run the script with the URL of the &rmt; server as a parameter."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: rmt_client.xml:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>sh rmt-client-setup https://<replaceable>RMT_SERVER</replaceable>/</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:222
#, no-c-format
msgid "Executing this script imports the &rmt; CA's certificate into the trusted store."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternatively, you can specify the correct fingerprint or path to the server certificate. For details, see <command>sh rmt-client-setup --help</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:233
#, no-c-format
msgid "The script downloads the server's CA certificate. Accept it by pressing <keycap>Y</keycap> . The tool now performs all necessary modifications to the client."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use <command>SUSEConnect</command> to add more products. For details, run <command>SUSEConnect --help</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:249
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring clients with &yast;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "To configure a client to perform the registration against an &rmt; server, use the &yast; <guimenu>Product Registration</guimenu> module <command>yast2 registration</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:257
#, no-c-format
msgid "On the client, the credentials are not necessary, and you may leave the relevant fields empty. Click <guimenu>Local Registration Server</guimenu> and enter its URL. Then click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> until the exit from the module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:265
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring clients for custom stand-alone repositories"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:267
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you created a custom stand-alone repository on the &rmt; server, it is not registered on client machines with <command>SUSEConnect</command> because it has no parent product."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add the repository manually, follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:279
#, no-c-format
msgid "Point your Web browser to the following RMT server URL:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: rmt_client.xml:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "https://<replaceable>RMT_SERVER_HOSTNAME/repo/</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:285
#, no-c-format
msgid "Navigate the browser through the directory structure to your custom repository's <filename>repodata/</filename> subdirectory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:291
#, no-c-format
msgid "On the client machine, add the discovered repository URL:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: rmt_client.xml:294
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper ar <replaceable>CUSTOM_REPO_URL</replaceable> <replaceable>CUSTOM_REPO_NAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "Listing accessible repositories"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "To list available modules and repositories, use <command>SUSEConnect --list-extensions</command> . Alternatively, you can also browse the directory listing of the &rmt; server by visiting <literal>https://<replaceable>RMT_SERVER</replaceable>/repo/</literal> and its subdirectories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: rmt_client.xml:310
#, no-c-format
msgid "Online migration of &sle; clients"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "&sle; clients registered to &rmt; can be migrated online to the latest service pack of the same major release the same way as clients registered to &scc;. Before starting the migration, make sure that &rmt; has the required products available and mirrored."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: rmt_client.xml:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "For detailed information on the online migration, see <xref linkend=\"cha-upgrade-paths\"/> ."
msgstr ""

